                            span#narrate-title-emotional Emotional Stress
                    p#narrate-1-emotional 
                        span In addition to the financial loss, the victims also experience severe emotional distress. The common emotional impacts: anxiety, shame, embarrassment, grief, guilt, depression, fear, anger, feelings of vulnerability, lack of trust in others, isolation.
                    p#narrate-2-emotional 
                        span Quotes from victims: “I don’t pick up the phone anymore. I’m scared” (Calgary grandmother who lost $17,000). Her daughter says “she is just so drained and distraught now” 
                    p#narrate-3-emotional
                        span “I was so scared. It’s the worst trauma that I have ever experienced in my life. I started questioning myself. Why me? I doubted myself. I still have nightmares” (Ottawa grandmother who lost $10,000)
                    p#narrate-4-emotional
                        span “It’s embarrassment and a total feeling of stupidity and, you know, we walk around saying it’s right across our forehead it says sucker, stupid, gullible” (Maryland man who lost $38,000)
